                            <comment id="72509" author="yujian" created="Fri, 29 Nov 2013 06:09:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patches also landed on Lustre b2_4 branch for 2.4.2.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="72374" author="yong.fan" created="Wed, 27 Nov 2013 07:48:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The patch has been landed to master.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="71742" author="yong.fan" created="Mon, 18 Nov 2013 01:32:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-4182&quot; title=&quot;sanity-scrub test_15: FAIL: (10) Failed to start OI scrub on mds1 &quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-4182&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-4182&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; is not the same issue, which was failed to start OI scrub because some instance already in running.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="70270" author="green" created="Wed, 30 Oct 2013 16:23:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;there&apos;s also &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-4182&quot; title=&quot;sanity-scrub test_15: FAIL: (10) Failed to start OI scrub on mds1 &quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-4182&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-4182&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; that has exactly the same error, but no interop&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="68476" author="yong.fan" created="Mon, 7 Oct 2013 06:08:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The patch for detecting 1.8 upgrade on b2_4:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/7625/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/7625/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The patch for dryrun OI scrub on b2_4:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/7867/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/7867/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The patch for skipping sanity-scrub test_15 (for older MDS) on master&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/7868/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/7868/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="68378" author="adilger" created="Fri, 4 Oct 2013 16:11:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Looks like this test should be skipped when running against an older Lustre (&amp;lt; 2.4.2) and the --dryrun patch &lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/7720&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/7720&lt;/a&gt; and upgrade patch &lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/7719&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/7719&lt;/a&gt; need to be backported to b2_4.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
